    "(7) Sensory Attribute Complexity and Food Matrix Limitations.",
    "The effectiveness of AI models in sensory prediction varies depending on the type of sensory attribute and the complexity of the food matrix.",
    "Attributes such as sweetness, saltiness, and bitterness are generally easier to model because they correspond to specific chemical markers and receptor mechanisms.",
    "In contrast, attributes like aroma nuance, mouthfeel, and texture involve complex perceptual pathways and multidimensional data, which make them more difficult to represent accurately.",
    "Similarly, the structure of the food matrix influences model performance."
  ],
